    <description>
        <p>Desktop application for NymVPN.</p>
        <p>
            NymVPN is a decentralized, mixnet and zero-knowledge VPN.
            Features:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>5-hop <em>Anonymous</em> mode (using the Nym Mixnet)</li>
            <li>2-hop <em>Fast</em> mode (using WireGuard)</li>
            <li>No centralized logs</li>
            <li>Hide your public IP</li>
            <li>Entry and exit hop location</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
            NOTE: This package only provides the <em>client</em> application.
            For the VPN to work, the daemon aka <code>nym-vpnd</code>,
            must be installed and running.
            You can install it from these separate packages:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>deb package (requires to setup the Nym deb repository): <code>nym-vpnd</code></li>
            <li>AUR packages: <code>nym-vpnd</code> and <code>nym-vpnd-bin</code></li>
        </ul>
        <p>For more details, please check https://nymvpn.com/en/download/linux</p>
        <p>
            Alternatively you can get the binary directly from the GitHub releases:
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to https://github.com/nymtech/nym-vpn-client/releases</li>
            <li>Find the latest release with tag <code>nym-vpn-core-v1.2.3</code></li>
            <li>Download the linux archive <code>nym-vpn-core-v1.2.3_linux_x86_64.tar.gz</code>
                and extract the binary (make it executable)</li>
            <li>From a terminal, run <code>sudo nym-vpnd</code></li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            NOTE: The daemon requires root privileges to work.
        </p>
    </description>
